    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. Can you expand on the idea of the \"single point of failure\"? I want to argue that even \"well-intentioned\" regulations—like those meant to stop misinformation—are just Trojan horses for censorship. Why is it philosophically impossible for a regulator to stay neutral?",
