      "content": "Philosophically, it is impossible for a regulator to stay neutral because power inevitably corrupts intent; even \"well-intentioned\" laws like those against misinformation are crafted by politicians who inevitably prioritize their own political agendas over objective truth. This creates a structural bias where the state becomes the ultimate arbiter of what is \"true,\" effectively allowing the government to censor any viewpoint that challenges official narratives while pretending to protect the public. Ultimately, granting the government the power to decide what speech is permissible transforms the internet from a marketplace of ideas into a state-controlled propaganda tool.",
